properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant rainfall expected early this morning. Further rainfall amounts of 10 to 20 mm are possible. Local total amounts up to 40 mm are possible in areas that receive a thunderstorm. The ground, already near saturation, has a lessened ability to absorb further rainfall. Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. The precipitation is from a strong low pressure system which will track into Quebec today. Showers will taper off through the middle of the day. For information concerning flooding, please consult your local conservation authority or Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry District Office. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A total of 25 to 40 millimetres of rain is expected by Friday evening. A low pressure system is bringing rain, at times heavy, over Quebec, which will continue on Friday. Total rainfall amounts approaching 50 millimetres are possible locally. Since spring freshet has not ended in many areas, flooding is possible in the most vulnerable areas. ### Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Rainfall warnings are issued when significant rainfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Rain at times heavy tonight. Additional precipitation amounts of 10 to 20 mm are expected. This rainfall is due to a low pressure system, which will track over Northeastern Ontario this evening. Rain will taper to drizzle overnight. The ground in some locations is already near saturation or remains partially frozen and as a result has little ability to absorb further rainfall. ### Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
